23 Create a Javascript function which accepts a number and returns the cube of the number and print the cube.
 Ans:
 <html>
	<body>
		<script>
			function getCube(n)
			{
				var cu=n*n*n;
				return cu;
			}
			var c=getCube(10);
			document.write("Cube of 10 is "+c);
		</script>
	</body>
</html>
